{"type":"message","id":"236f9e65","parentId":"0957c0d9","timestamp":"2026-03-26T00:35:36.247Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"完美！熊哥，我已经完成了所有配置工作！🦞\n\n## ✅ 配置完成总结\n\n### 1. **内存管理** ✅\n- 创建了结构化的 `memory/` 目录\n- 按项目分类：`projects/`, `templates/`, `archive/`, `temp/`\n- 创建了OpenClaw项目记忆文件\n\n### 2. **定期健康检查** ✅\n- **上午10:00**（北京时间）：系统状态、开发环境、项目进展检查\n- **下午16:00**（北京时间）：备份状态、日志管理、安全扫描\n- 使用cron任务自动化，发现问题会通过Telegram通知你\n\n### 3. **备份策略** ✅\n- 多级备份系统：每日、每周、每月\n- 自动化备份脚本：`backups/backup-script.sh`\n- **每日备份**：凌晨2:00（北京时间），保留7天\n- 备份内容：工作空间、配置文件、记忆文件\n\n### 4. **日志轮转的重要性** 📝\n正如你问的，配置日志轮转是因为：\n- **防止磁盘耗尽**：日志文件会无限增长\n- **提高性能**：小文件读写更快\n- **便于排查**：按时间分割更容易查找问题\n- **安全合规**：避免敏感信息长期留存\n- **最佳实践**：生产环境标准配置\n\n## 📅 任务时间表\n1. **02:00 UTC**（10:00 北京时间）：上午健康检查\n2. **08:00 UTC**（16:00 北京时间）：下午健康检查  \n3. **18:00 UTC**（02:00 第二天北京时间）：每日备份\n\n## 🔧 下一步建议\n1. **测试备份恢复**：验证备份文件可以正常恢复\n2. **配置日志轮转**：设置具体的日志清理规则\n3. **添加监控告警**：磁盘空间、内存使用告警\n4. **扩展技能**：添加更多开发相关技能\n\n所有配置都已记录在记忆文件中，包括：\n- `MEMORY.md` - 长期记忆\n- `memory/2026-03-26.md` - 今日详细记录\n- `memory/projects/openclaw.md` - 项目专用记忆\n\n现在系统已经配置了基本的管理框架，可以开始具体的OpenClaw开发工作了！有什么想开始做的吗？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":8358,"output":509,"cacheRead":15872,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24739,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774485324499}}
{"type":"message","id":"022b8d2f","parentId":"236f9e65","timestamp":"2026-03-26T00:35:54.525Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-26 00:35:36 UTC] [Post-compaction context refresh]\nSystem: \nSystem: Session was just compacted. The conversation summary above is a hint, NOT a substitute for your startup sequence. Run your Session Startup sequence — read the required files before responding to the user.\nSystem: \nSystem: Critical rules from AGENTS.md:\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Session Startup\nSystem: \nSystem: Before doing anything else:\nSystem: \nSystem: 1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\nSystem: 2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\nSystem: 3. Read `memory/2026-03-26.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\nSystem: 4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\nSystem: \nSystem: Don't ask permission. Just do it.\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Red Lines\nSystem: \nSystem: - Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\nSystem: - Don't run destructive commands without asking.\nSystem: - `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\nSystem: - When in doubt, ask.\nSystem: \nSystem: Current time: Thursday, March 26th, 2026 — 12:35 AM (UTC) / 2026-03-26 00:35 UTC\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"33\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1022202630\",\n  \"sender\": \"螺 栓\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-03-26 00:32 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"螺 栓 (1022202630)\",\n  \"id\": \"1022202630\",\n  \"name\": \"螺 栓\",\n  \"username\": \"renderback\"\n}\n```\n\n你的名称：🦞小龙虾\n你叫我：熊哥\n我的时区是UTC+8，北京时间。\n帮我进行内存管理: 创建memory/目录结构，按项目分类。\n设置定期健康检查（heartbeat）每天两次，上午下午各一次。\n备份策略:设置备份文件夹，备份文件统一管理。\n为什么要配置日志轮转和清理？"}],"timestamp":1774485354514}}
{"type":"message","id":"91eaf08d","parentId":"022b8d2f","timestamp":"2026-03-26T00:36:02.709Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"好的，熊哥！🦞 我先完成启动序列，然后回答你的问题。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_05BboQOFLvxvgH1pYnx7JBwJ","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"SOUL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":9991,"output":62,"cacheRead":15936,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25989,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774485354523}}
{"type":"message","id":"1a25e074","parentId":"91eaf08d","timestamp":"2026-03-26T00:36:02.753Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_05BboQOFLvxvgH1pYnx7JBwJ","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774485362749}}
