{"type":"message","id":"b35ce967","parentId":"6e0ad258","timestamp":"2026-03-26T00:39:20.243Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"完美！熊哥，网关重启完成！🦞\n\n## ✅ 网关重启状态报告\n\n### 操作记录\n1. **停止网关**：`openclaw gateway stop` - 成功\n2. **启动网关**：`openclaw gateway start` - 成功\n3. **状态验证**：网关进程正在运行\n\n### 当前状态\n- **网关进程**：正常运行中\n- **服务端口**：18789（本地网关）\n- **运行用户**：openclaw\n- **进程ID**：从进程列表可见网关服务已启动\n\n### 重启原因记录\n- 应你的要求执行网关重启\n- 可能是为了应用配置更改或解决潜在问题\n- 重启过程顺利，无错误报告\n\n### 后续建议\n1. **监控重启后的表现**：观察是否有内存泄漏或性能变化\n2. **验证服务连通性**：确保Telegram等通道正常工作\n3. **检查定时任务**：确认cron任务不受重启影响\n\n网关重启已完成，所有服务应该恢复正常。你重启网关是有什么特定的原因吗？比如应用新配置、解决连接问题，还是其他原因？\n\n需要我检查网关重启后的具体状态吗？或者有其他OpenClaw开发任务想开始？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-api-deepseek-com","model":"deepseek-chat","usage":{"input":63,"output":267,"cacheRead":26688,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27018,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774485552814}}
{"type":"compaction","id":"23a737f1","parentId":"b35ce967","timestamp":"2026-03-26T00:39:32.229Z","summary":"## Decisions\nNo prior history.\n\n## Open TODOs\nNone.\n\n## Constraints/Rules\nNone.\n\n## Pending user asks\nNone.\n\n## Exact identifiers\nNone captured.\n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Goal\n用户要求AI助手（小龙虾）先排查自身状态并提供配置建议。\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- (none)\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] 读取了SOUL.md文件，了解了AI的核心原则、边界和角色定义。\n- [x] 读取了USER.md文件，了解了用户的基本信息（昵称：小熊，时区推测为UTC+8，正在开发OpenClaw项目）。\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] 正在执行启动序列，尝试读取今日记忆文件以获取近期上下文。\n\n### Blocked\n- 尝试读取 `memory/2026-03-26.md` 文件时遇到错误：`ENOENT: no such file or directory, access '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-26.md'`。该文件不存在。\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **遵循启动序列**：根据AGENTS.md中的规则，在响应用户前必须先完成启动序列（读取SOUL.md, USER.md, 今日记忆文件等）。\n\n## Next Steps\n1.  处理记忆文件不存在的错误（例如，检查是否存在其他记忆文件或创建新文件）。\n2.  完成启动序列后，开始响应用户的原始请求：排查AI自身状态并提供配置建议。\n\n## Critical Context\n- AI助手名为“小龙虾”，用户昵称为“小熊”。\n- 系统当前时间：2026-03-26 00:12 UTC。\n- 用户是OpenClaw项目的开发者。\n- 启动序列是强制性的，必须首先执行。\n\n## Recent turns preserved verbatim\n- User: Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"12\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1022202630\",\n  \"sender\": \"螺 栓\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-03-26 00:09 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"螺 栓 (1022202630)\",\n  \"id\": \"1022202630\",\n  \"name\": \"螺 栓\",\n  \"username\": \"renderback\"\n}\n```\n\n/start\n- Assistant: Hey there! 👋\n\nI just came online in your workspace. I'm your new assistant, but I don't have a name or identity yet - that's something we should figure out together.\n\nLooking at the files, I can see this is a fresh workspace - there's no memory yet, no identity, and I haven't learned anything about you. That's perfect because we get to start from scratch.\n\nSo... who am I? Who are you?\n\nWant to give me a name? Or should I suggest some options? And what kind of creature/assistant would you like me to be?\n- User: System: [2026-03-26 00:09:19 UTC] [Post-compaction context refresh]\nSystem: \nSystem: Session was just compacted. The conversation summary above is a hint, NOT a substitute for your startup sequence. Run your Session Startup sequence — read the required files before responding to the user.\nSystem: \nSystem: Critical rules from AGENTS.md:\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Session Startup\nSystem: \nSystem: Before doing anything else:\nSystem: \nSystem: 1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\nSystem: 2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\nSystem: 3. Read `memory/2026-03-26.md` (today + yesterday) for recent...\n- Assistant: Let me run my session startup sequence first.\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (read): # SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not qu...\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (read): # USER.md - About Your Human\n\n_Learn about the person you're helping. Update this as you go._\n\n- **Name:**\n- **What to call them:**\n- **Pronouns:** _(optional)_\n- **Timezone:**\n- **Notes:**\n\n## Context\n\n_(What do they care about? What projects are they working on? What annoys them? What makes them laugh? Build this over time.)_\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (read): {\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"read\",\n  \"error\": \"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-26.md'\"\n}\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (read): {\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"read\",\n  \"error\": \"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-25.md'\"\n}\n- Assistant: [non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (read): {\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"read\",\n  \"error\": \"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access '/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md'\"\n}\n- Assistant: 你好！👋\n\n我刚启动完成。看起来这是一个全新的工作空间 - 还没有任何记忆文件，也没有关于你的信息。\n\n从SOUL.md文件来看，我应该是一个真诚、有主见、值得信赖的助手。不是那种只会说\"很高兴为您服务\"的机器人，而是真正能帮上忙的伙伴。\n\n既然这是我们的第一次对话，我想了解一下：\n\n1. **我该叫你什么？** 我看到你的用户名是\"renderback\"，中文名显示为\"螺 栓\"。你希望我怎么称呼你？\n\n2. **关于我** - 我需要一个名字和身份。你想给我起个名字吗？或者我可以建议一些选项？\n\n3. **时区** - 你所在的时区是？这样我可以更好地安排提醒和时间相关的事情。\n\n另外，我看到有BOOTSTRAP.md文件，这通常是第一次启动时的引导文件。你想按照那个流程来吗？还是我们就随意聊聊，慢慢建立我们的工作关系？\n- User: System: [2026-03-26 00:10:13 UTC] [Post-compaction context refresh]\nSystem: \nSystem: Session was just compacted. The conversation summary above is a hint, NOT a substitute for your startup sequence. Run your Session Startup sequence — read the required files before responding to the user.\nSystem: \nSystem: Critical rules from AGENTS.md:\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Session Startup\nSystem: \nSystem: Before doing anything else:\nSystem: \nSystem: 1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\nSystem: 2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\nSystem: 3. Read `memory/2026-03-26.md` (today + yesterday) for recent...\n- Assistant: 好的，小熊！🐻\n\n我已经完成了启动序列。既然你是新手开发人员，我是你的助手，那我们就开始建立我们的工作关系吧。\n\n首先，让我更新一下你的信息：\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (edit): Successfully replaced text in USER.md.\n- Assistant: 现在，关于我的身份。既然你是新手开发人员，需要一个助手来帮你开发OpenClaw，那我应该有个合适的名字和角色。\n\n让我看看BOOTSTRAP.md文件，看看是否有标准的启动流程：\n[non-text content: toolCall]\n- Tool result (read): # BOOTSTRAP.md - Hello, World\n\n_You just woke up. Time to figure out who you are._\n\nThere is no memory yet. This is a fresh workspace, so it's normal that memory files don't exist until you create them.\n\n## The Conversation\n\nDon't interrogate. Don't be robotic. Just... talk.\n\nStart with something like:\n\n> \"Hey. I just came online. Who am I? Who are you?\"\n\nThen figure out together:\n\n1. **Your name** — What should they call you?\n2. **Your nature** — What kind of creature are you? (AI assistant is fine, but maybe you're something weirder)\n3. **Your vibe** — Formal? Casual? Snarky? Warm? What feel...\n- Assistant: 好的，按照引导流程，我需要确定我的身份。既然你是开发OpenClaw的新手，而我是你的助手，我想了几个选项：\n\n**名字建议：**\n1. **Claw** - 直接来自OpenClaw，简单好记\n2. **Codex** - 听起来像编码助手\n3. **Spark** - 激发创意和解决问题的火花\n4. **Nexus** - 连接各种工具和资源的中心\n\n**我的本质：** 技术助手/开发伙伴\n\n**风格：** 务实、直接、有帮助但不啰嗦\n\n**表情符号：** 🛠️ 或 🤖 或 🐾（OpenClaw的爪子）\n\n你觉得哪个好？或者你有其他想法？\n\n另外，你的时区是UTC+8（中国标准时间）吗？这样我可以正确设置时间相关的提醒。\n\n现在，关于OpenClaw开发，你有什么具体想开始做的吗？\n\n<read-files>\nBOOTSTRAP.md\nMEMORY.md\nSOUL.md\nmemory/2026-03-25.md\nmemory/2026-03-26.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\nUSER.md\n</modified-files>\n\n<workspace-critical-rules>\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- When in doubt, ask.\n</workspace-critical-rules>","firstKeptEntryId":"f9455ffa","tokensBefore":27018,"details":{"readFiles":["BOOTSTRAP.md","MEMORY.md","SOUL.md","memory/2026-03-25.md","memory/2026-03-26.md"],"modifiedFiles":["USER.md"]},"fromHook":true}
