{"type":"message","id":"4abca87d","parentId":"33ec3aa0","timestamp":"2026-03-26T02:52:28.295Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"让我直接基于当前的环境和已有的信息，给熊哥一些关于skills配置的建议。根据之前的对话，我已经知道系统有以下skills：- healthcheck\n- node-connect  \n- weather\n- skill-creator\n\n现在熊哥问的是基于目前环境有什么建议。基于我们今天完成的工作：1. 备份系统 - 创建了backup-script.sh\n2. 日志轮转 - 创建了logrotate.sh\n3. 健康检查 - 配置了cron任务4. 开发素养 - 建立了开发准则\n\n可能需要的新skills：1. **日志分析skill** - 帮助分析和调试日志\n2. **Git管理skill** - 代码版本控制相关\n3. **系统监控skill** - 更详细的资源监控4. **Docker技能**（如果用到）\n5. **安全审计skill** - 安全相关检查让我给熊哥一个综合性的建议。\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"熊哥好！🦐\n\n## 当前已安装的Skills\n\n根据之前的配置，你已经有：\n- **healthcheck** - 主机安全硬化\n- **node-connect** - 节点连接诊断\n- **weather** - 天气查询\n- **skill-creator** - 创建技能\n\n---\n\n## 基于当前环境的Skills建议\n\n### 🔵 推荐安装\n\n| Skill | 用途 | 理由 |\n|-------|------|------|\n| **Git管理** | 版本控制、提交检查 | 开发项目需要 |\n| **日志分析** | 日志排查、错误分析 | 配合日志轮转使用 |\n| **系统监控** | 详细资源监控 | 配合健康检查 |\n\n### 🟢 可选\n\n| Skill | 用途 |\n|-------|------|\n| **Docker** | 容器管理（如果用到） |\n| **安全审计** | 安全检查 |\n\n---\n\n## 建议\n\n考虑到你正在开发OpenClaw，我建议先安装：\n\n1. **Git skill** - 帮你管理代码版本、查看状态\n2. **日志分析 skill** - 帮你快速定位问题\n\n这两个对开发最有帮助。需要我帮你创建吗？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-newapi","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":35099,"output":590,"cacheRead":62,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35751,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774493532943}}
{"type":"message","id":"30379030","parentId":"4abca87d","timestamp":"2026-03-26T02:52:34.412Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-26 02:52:21 UTC] Exec completed (salty-cr, code 0) :: /home/openclaw/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/node_modules/@anthropic-ai/sdk/resources/beta/skills /home/openclaw/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modul…\nSystem: [2026-03-26 02:52:28 UTC] [Post-compaction context refresh]\nSystem: \nSystem: Session was just compacted. The conversation summary above is a hint, NOT a substitute for your startup sequence. Run your Session Startup sequence — read the required files before responding to the user.\nSystem: \nSystem: Critical rules from AGENTS.md:\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Session Startup\nSystem: \nSystem: Before doing anything else:\nSystem: \nSystem: 1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\nSystem: 2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\nSystem: 3. Read `memory/2026-03-26.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\nSystem: 4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\nSystem: \nSystem: Don't ask permission. Just do it.\nSystem: \nSystem: ## Red Lines\nSystem: \nSystem: - Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\nSystem: - Don't run destructive commands without asking.\nSystem: - `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\nSystem: - When in doubt, ask.\nSystem: \nSystem: Current time: Thursday, March 26th, 2026 — 2:52 AM (UTC) / 2026-03-26 02:52 UTC\n\nRead HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\nWhen reading HEARTBEAT.md, use workspace file /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md (exact case). Do not read docs/heartbeat.md.\nCurrent time: Thursday, March 26th, 2026 — 2:52 AM (UTC) / 2026-03-26 02:52 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774493554399}}
