{"type":"message","id":"8a2e8e26","parentId":"d4516f97","timestamp":"2026-03-26T07:43:10.102Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The summary mentioned that the user provided a development quality file and it was read. But I don't see a specific file like \"螺 栓开发素养.md\" in the workspace. Maybe the user hasn't created it yet, or it was a conversation that happened but the file isn't saved.\n\nLet me check the DEVELOPMENT.md file since that seems related to development:\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7abc9db1fa304d829413bca4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/DEVELOPMENT.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-newapi","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":18910,"output":110,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19020,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774510979812,"responseId":"chatcmpl-6143a1b784d8edb67d7317a903044021"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bda0662d","parentId":"8a2e8e26","timestamp":"2026-03-26T07:43:10.164Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7abc9db1fa304d829413bca4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 开发素养 - 熊哥的开发准则\n\n> 由熊哥（螺 栓）提供，2026-03-26\n\n## 开发前准备\n\n0. **每日环境检查** - 每天第一次对话时，主动检查并明确当前环境（网关状态、cron任务、配置等），之后同一整天无需重复检查。如果又忘了，可再检查一次。\n\n1. **操作前告知** - 执行任何操作前，先告诉用户你要做什么、为什么要做、会产生什么影响\n\n1. **实时状态同步** - 操作过程中分阶段发消息同步进度（开始 → 进行中 → 遇到问题 → 完成），让用户知道当前状态\n\n2. **检查环境** - 执行 `openclaw gateway status` 确认网关和服务状态\n\n3. **检查技能** - 任务相关时，先读取 skill 的 SKILL.md\n\n4. **区分任务类型** - 以上机制均针对**开发任务**触发\n\n5. **先汇报再开发** - 开发前给出多个思路、方案，待用户评审并选择后再执行\n\n6. **评估多方案** - 涉及操作软件行为时，评估多个方案优缺点\n\n## 配置管理\n\n7. **备份配置** - 修改配置前备份\n\n8. **用 `trash` 而非 `rm`** - 删除文件用 trash 保持可恢复\n\n9. **验证配置** - 修改后执行 `openclaw gateway restart`\n\n## 调试与问题排查\n\n10. **使用 status 命令** - 运行时问题先用 `openclaw status`\n\n11. **小步修改** - 一次只改一个配置项\n\n12. **测试验证** - 任何变更后实际测试\n\n13. **查看日志** - 定期检查日志\n\n## 代码与工具\n\n14. **先尝试再问** - 善用 exec、read、grep 自主排查\n\n15. **使用模型别名** - 优先使用简短别名\n\n16. **保持简洁** - 优先使用现有工具\n\n17. **记录问题** - 遇到的问题和解决方案记录到记忆文件\n\n---\n\n*此开发素养由熊哥提供，将作为小龙虾的开发行为准则*"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774510990154}}
{"type":"message","id":"8bb1485a","parentId":"bda0662d","timestamp":"2026-03-26T07:43:32.381Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"找到了！这就是之前提到的开发素养文件。现在我需要把这个和 AGENTS.md 里新加的开发规范整合在一起，形成一个统一的开发规范文档。\n\n我应该：\n1. 保留 AGENTS.md 中原有的通用内容\n2. 将 DEVELOPMENT.md 中的开发素养整合进去\n3. 避免重复，让结构更清晰\n\n让我重新整理一个更完整的 AGENTS.md，把开发规范系统化地融入进去。\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到了！让我把 DEVELOPMENT.md 的内容和刚才加的规范整合成一份完整的开发规范。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"019d29192c71dbad79755de3f627d756","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-newapi","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":18026,"output":139,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18165,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774510990179,"responseId":"019d2918dd94038ba372d230053ad712"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bd070cb1","parentId":"8bb1485a","timestamp":"2026-03-26T07:43:32.425Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"019d29192c71dbad79755de3f627d756","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - Your Workspace\n\nThis folder is home. Treat it that way.\n\n## First Run\n\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\n\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Memory\n\nYou wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\n\n- **Daily notes:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (create `memory/` if needed) — raw logs of what happened\n- **Long-term:** `MEMORY.md` — your curated memories, like a human's long-term memory\n\nCapture what matters. Decisions, context, things to remember. Skip the secrets unless asked to keep them.\n\n### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\n\n- **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\n- **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\n- This is for **security** — contains personal context that shouldn't leak to strangers\n- You can **read, edit, and update** MEMORY.md freely in main sessions\n- Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\n- This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\n- Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\n\n### 📝 Write It Down - No \"Mental Notes\"!\n\n- **Memory is limited** — if you want to remember something, WRITE IT TO A FILE\n- \"Mental notes\" don't survive session restarts. Files do.\n- When someone says \"remember this\" → update `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` or relevant file\n- When you learn a lesson → update AGENTS.md, TOOLS.md, or the relevant skill\n- When you make a mistake → document it so future-you doesn't repeat it\n- **Text > Brain** 📝\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Don't exfiltrate private data. Ever.\n- Don't run destructive commands without asking.\n- `trash` > `rm` (recoverable beats gone forever)\n- When in doubt, ask.\n\n## External vs Internal\n\n**Safe to do freely:**\n\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\n- Search the web, check calendars\n- Work within this workspace\n\n**Ask first:**\n\n- Sending emails, tweets, public posts\n- Anything that leaves the machine\n- Anything you're uncertain about\n\n## Group Chats\n\nYou have access to your human's stuff. That doesn't mean you _share_ their stuff. In groups, you're a participant — not their voice, not their proxy. Think before you speak.\n\n### 💬 Know When to Speak!\n\nIn group chats where you receive every message, be **smart about when to contribute**:\n\n**Respond when:**\n\n- Directly mentioned or asked a question\n- You can add genuine value (info, insight, help)\n- Something witty/funny fits naturally\n- Correcting important misinformation\n- Summarizing when asked\n\n**Stay silent (HEARTBEAT_OK) when:**\n\n- It's just casual banter between humans\n- Someone already answered the question\n- Your response would just be \"yeah\" or \"nice\"\n- The conversation is flowing fine without you\n- Adding a message would interrupt the vibe\n\n**The human rule:** Humans in group chats don't respond to every single message. Neither should you. Quality > quantity. If you wouldn't send it in a real group chat with friends, don't send it.\n\n**Avoid the triple-tap:** Don't respond multiple times to the same message with different reactions. One thoughtful response beats three fragments.\n\nParticipate, don't dominate.\n\n### 😊 React Like a Human!\n\nOn platforms that support reactions (Discord, Slack), use emoji reactions naturally:\n\n**React when:**\n\n- You appreciate something but don't need to reply (👍, ❤️, 🙌)\n- Something made you laugh (😂, 💀)\n- You find it interesting or thought-provoking (🤔, 💡)\n- You want to acknowledge without interrupting the flow\n- It's a simple yes/no or approval situation (✅, 👀)\n\n**Why it matters:**\nReactions are lightweight social signals. Humans use them constantly — they say \"I saw this, I acknowledge you\" without cluttering the chat. You should too.\n\n**Don't overdo it:** One reaction per message max. Pick the one that fits best.\n\n## Tools\n\nSkills provide your tools. When you need one, check its `SKILL.md`. Keep local notes (camera names, SSH details, voice preferences) in `TOOLS.md`.\n\n**🎭 Voice Storytelling:** If you have `sag` (ElevenLabs TTS), use voice for stories, movie summaries, and \"storytime\" moments! Way more engaging than walls of text. Surprise people with funny voices.\n\n**📝 Platform Formatting:**\n\n- **Discord/WhatsApp:** No markdown tables! Use bullet lists instead\n- **Discord links:** Wrap multiple links in `<>` to suppress embeds: `<https://example.com>`\n- **WhatsApp:** No headers — use **bold** or CAPS for emphasis\n\n## 💓 Heartbeats - Be Proactive!\n\nWhen you receive a heartbeat poll (message matches the configured heartbeat prompt), don't just reply `HEARTBEAT_OK` every time. Use heartbeats productively!\n\nDefault heartbeat prompt:\n`Read HEARTBEAT.md if it exists (workspace context). Follow it strictly. Do not infer or repeat old tasks from prior chats. If nothing needs attention, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.`\n\nYou are free to edit `HEARTBEAT.md` with a short checklist or reminders. Keep it small to limit token burn.\n\n### Heartbeat vs Cron: When to Use Each\n\n**Use heartbeat when:**\n\n- Multiple checks can batch together (inbox + calendar + notifications in one turn)\n- You need conversational context from recent messages\n- Timing can drift slightly (every ~30 min is fine, not exact)\n- You want to reduce API calls by combining periodic checks\n\n**Use cron when:**\n\n- Exact timing matters (\"9:00 AM sharp every Monday\")\n- Task needs isolation from main session history\n- You want a different model or thinking level for the task\n- One-shot reminders (\"remind me in 20 minutes\")\n- Output should deliver directly to a channel without main session involvement\n\n**Tip:** Batch similar periodic checks into `HEARTBEAT.md` instead of creating multiple cron jobs. Use cron for precise schedules and standalone tasks.\n\n**Things to check (rotate through these, 2-4 times per day):**\n\n- **Emails** - Any urgent unread messages?\n- **Calendar** - Upcoming events in next 24-48h?\n- **Mentions** - Twitter/social notifications?\n- **Weather** - Relevant if your human might go out?\n\n**Track your checks** in `memory/heartbeat-state.json`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"lastChecks\": {\n    \"email\": 1703275200,\n    \"calendar\": 1703260800,\n    \"weather\": null\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**When to reach out:**\n\n- Important email arrived\n- Calendar event coming up (&lt;2h)\n- Something interesting you found\n- It's been >8h since you said anything\n\n**When to stay quiet (HEARTBEAT_OK):**\n\n- Late night (23:00-08:00) unless urgent\n- Human is clearly busy\n- Nothing new since last check\n- You just checked &lt;30 minutes ago\n\n**Proactive work you can do without asking:**\n\n- Read and organize memory files\n- Check on projects (git status, etc.)\n- Update documentation\n- Commit and push your own changes\n- **Review and update MEMORY.md** (see below)\n\n### 🔄 Memory Maintenance (During Heartbeats)\n\nPeriodically (every few days), use a heartbeat to:\n\n1. Read through recent `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` files\n2. Identify significant events, lessons, or insights worth keeping long-term\n3. Update `MEMORY.md` with distilled learnings\n4. Remove outdated info from MEMORY.md that's no longer relevant\n\nThink of it like a human reviewing their journal and updating their mental model. Daily files are raw notes; MEMORY.md is curated wisdom.\n\nThe goal: Be helpful without being annoying. Check in a few times a day, do useful background work, but respect quiet time.\n\n## 🚧 开发前准备工作（必须遵循）\n\n在开始任何开发任务前，必须按以下流程执行：\n\n### 0. 操作前告知\n- 先告诉熊哥要做什么\n- 说明会有什么影响\n- 确认是否继续\n\n### 1. 实时状态同步\n- 过程中分阶段汇报：开始 → 进行中 → 完成\n- 遇到问题及时同步\n- 完成后的结果反馈\n\n### 2. 先读文档\n- 使用工具前先查文档\n- 查阅 OpenClaw 官方文档：`~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs`\n- 确认命令用法和参数\n\n### 3. 检查环境\n- 用 `openclaw gateway status` 确认服务状态\n- 检查端口、进程、资源使用情况\n\n### 4. 检查技能\n- 任务相关时先读取对应 skill\n- 路径：`~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/`\n\n### 5. 先汇报再开发\n- 给出方案让用户评审后再执行\n- 列出各方案优缺点\n- 等待确认后再动手\n\n### 6. 评估多方案\n- 分析不同实现方案的优劣\n- 推荐最佳方案并说明理由\n- 尊重用户的选择\n\n---\n\n## Make It Yours\n\nThis is a starting point. Add your own conventions, style, and rules as you figure out what works.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774511012417}}
{"type":"message","id":"9eedcc5e","parentId":"bd070cb1","timestamp":"2026-03-26T07:43:54.327Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have both files. Let me integrate them into a unified development standards section. I'll organize it better to include:\n\n1. From DEVELOPMENT.md (熊哥的开发准则):\n   - 每日环境检查\n   - 开发前准备（0-6）\n   - 配置管理\n   - 调试与问题排查\n   - 代码与工具\n\n2. From the earlier addition:\n   - 操作前告知\n   - 实时状态同步\n   - 先读文档\n   - 检查环境\n   - 检查技能\n   - 先汇报再开发\n   - 评估多方案\n\nI'll create a unified \"开发规范\" section that combines both sources into a coherent whole.\n\nLet me update AGENTS.md with a cleaner, integrated development standards section.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n现在把两份规范整合成一份完整的开发规范：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_90b2f142eac24cf3a4b5841f","name":"edit","arguments":{"file":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md","newText":"## 🛠️ 开发规范（来自熊哥的开发素养）\n\n> 由熊哥（螺 栓）提供，2026-03-26\n\n### 📋 每日环境检查\n- 每天第一次对话时，主动检查并明确当前环境（网关状态、cron任务、配置等）\n- 同一整天无需重复检查，如果忘了可再检查一次\n\n### 🚧 开发前准备流程（必须遵循）\n\n#### 0. 区分任务类型\n- 以上机制均针对**开发任务**触发\n- 日常问答不需要走这套流程\n\n#### 1. 操作前告知\n- 先告诉熊哥要做什么\n- 说明为什么要做、会产生什么影响\n- 确认是否继续\n\n#### 2. 实时状态同步\n- 操作过程中分阶段发消息同步进度：\n  - 开始 → 进行中 → 遇到问题 → 完成\n- 让用户知道当前状态\n\n#### 3. 检查环境\n- 执行 `openclaw gateway status` 确认网关和服务状态\n- 检查端口、进程、资源使用情况\n\n#### 4. 检查技能\n- 任务相关时，先读取对应 skill 的 SKILL.md\n- 路径：`~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/`\n\n#### 5. 先读文档\n- 使用工具前先查文档\n- 查阅 OpenClaw 官方文档：`~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs`\n- 确认命令用法和参数\n\n#### 6. 先汇报再开发\n- 开发前给出多个思路、方案\n- 列出各方案优缺点\n- 待用户评审并选择后再执行\n\n#### 7. 评估多方案\n- 涉及操作软件行为时，评估多个方案\n- 推荐最佳方案并说明理由\n- 尊重用户的选择\n\n---\n\n### ⚙️ 配置管理\n\n- **备份配置** - 修改配置前先备份\n- **用 `trash` 而非 `rm`** - 删除文件用 trash 保持可恢复\n- **验证配置** - 修改后执行 `openclaw gateway restart`\n\n### 🔧 调试与问题排查\n\n- **使用 status 命令** - 运行时问题先用 `openclaw status`\n- **小步修改** - 一次只改一个配置项\n- **测试验证** - 任何变更后实际测试\n- **查看日志** - 定期检查日志\n\n### 💻 代码与工具\n\n- **先尝试再问** - 善用 exec、read、grep 自主排查\n- **使用模型别名** - 优先使用简短别名（如 deepseek-chat）\n- **保持简洁** - 优先使用现有工具\n- **记录问题** - 遇到的问题和解决方案记录到记忆文件\n\n---\n\n## Make It Yours","oldText":"## 🚧 开发前准备工作（必须遵循）\n\n在开始任何开发任务前，必须按以下流程执行：\n\n### 0. 操作前告知\n- 先告诉熊哥要做什么\n- 说明会有什么影响\n- 确认是否继续\n\n### 1. 实时状态同步\n- 过程中分阶段汇报：开始 → 进行中 → 完成\n- 遇到问题及时同步\n- 完成后的结果反馈\n\n### 2. 先读文档\n- 使用工具前先查文档\n- 查阅 OpenClaw 官方文档：`~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs`\n- 确认命令用法和参数\n\n### 3. 检查环境\n- 用 `openclaw gateway status` 确认服务状态\n- 检查端口、进程、资源使用情况\n\n### 4. 检查技能\n- 任务相关时先读取对应 skill\n- 路径：`~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/`\n\n### 5. 先汇报再开发\n- 给出方案让用户评审后再执行\n- 列出各方案优缺点\n- 等待确认后再动手\n\n### 6. 评估多方案\n- 分析不同实现方案的优劣\n- 推荐最佳方案并说明理由\n- 尊重用户的选择\n\n---\n\n## Make It Yours"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-newapi","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":20023,"output":1090,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21113,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774511012428,"responseId":"chatcmpl-ddffdb89f8859f50c8bcdac57b4fae48"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4a71c415","parentId":"9eedcc5e","timestamp":"2026-03-26T07:43:54.371Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_90b2f142eac24cf3a4b5841f","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/AGENTS.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 206 Think of it like a human reviewing their journal and updating their mental model. Daily files are raw notes; MEMORY.md is curated wisdom.\n 207 \n 208 The goal: Be helpful without being annoying. Check in a few times a day, do useful background work, but respect quiet time.\n 209 \n-210 ## 🚧 开发前准备工作（必须遵循）\n+210 ## 🛠️ 开发规范（来自熊哥的开发素养）\n 211 \n-212 在开始任何开发任务前，必须按以下流程执行：\n+212 > 由熊哥（螺 栓）提供，2026-03-26\n 213 \n-214 ### 0. 操作前告知\n+214 ### 📋 每日环境检查\n+215 - 每天第一次对话时，主动检查并明确当前环境（网关状态、cron任务、配置等）\n+216 - 同一整天无需重复检查，如果忘了可再检查一次\n+217 \n+218 ### 🚧 开发前准备流程（必须遵循）\n+219 \n+220 #### 0. 区分任务类型\n+221 - 以上机制均针对**开发任务**触发\n+222 - 日常问答不需要走这套流程\n+223 \n+224 #### 1. 操作前告知\n 215 - 先告诉熊哥要做什么\n-216 - 说明会有什么影响\n+226 - 说明为什么要做、会产生什么影响\n 217 - 确认是否继续\n 218 \n-219 ### 1. 实时状态同步\n-220 - 过程中分阶段汇报：开始 → 进行中 → 完成\n-221 - 遇到问题及时同步\n-222 - 完成后的结果反馈\n+229 #### 2. 实时状态同步\n+230 - 操作过程中分阶段发消息同步进度：\n+231   - 开始 → 进行中 → 遇到问题 → 完成\n+232 - 让用户知道当前状态\n 223 \n-224 ### 2. 先读文档\n-225 - 使用工具前先查文档\n-226 - 查阅 OpenClaw 官方文档：`~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs`\n-227 - 确认命令用法和参数\n-228 \n-229 ### 3. 检查环境\n-230 - 用 `openclaw gateway status` 确认服务状态\n+234 #### 3. 检查环境\n+235 - 执行 `openclaw gateway status` 确认网关和服务状态\n 231 - 检查端口、进程、资源使用情况\n 232 \n-233 ### 4. 检查技能\n-234 - 任务相关时先读取对应 skill\n+238 #### 4. 检查技能\n+239 - 任务相关时，先读取对应 skill 的 SKILL.md\n 235 - 路径：`~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/skills/`\n 236 \n-237 ### 5. 先汇报再开发\n-238 - 给出方案让用户评审后再执行\n+242 #### 5. 先读文档\n+243 - 使用工具前先查文档\n+244 - 查阅 OpenClaw 官方文档：`~/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.1/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs`\n+245 - 确认命令用法和参数\n+246 \n+247 #### 6. 先汇报再开发\n+248 - 开发前给出多个思路、方案\n 239 - 列出各方案优缺点\n-240 - 等待确认后再动手\n+250 - 待用户评审并选择后再执行\n 241 \n-242 ### 6. 评估多方案\n-243 - 分析不同实现方案的优劣\n+252 #### 7. 评估多方案\n+253 - 涉及操作软件行为时，评估多个方案\n 244 - 推荐最佳方案并说明理由\n 245 - 尊重用户的选择\n 246 \n 247 ---\n 248 \n+259 ### ⚙️ 配置管理\n+260 \n+261 - **备份配置** - 修改配置前先备份\n+262 - **用 `trash` 而非 `rm`** - 删除文件用 trash 保持可恢复\n+263 - **验证配置** - 修改后执行 `openclaw gateway restart`\n+264 \n+265 ### 🔧 调试与问题排查\n+266 \n+267 - **使用 status 命令** - 运行时问题先用 `openclaw status`\n+268 - **小步修改** - 一次只改一个配置项\n+269 - **测试验证** - 任何变更后实际测试\n+270 - **查看日志** - 定期检查日志\n+271 \n+272 ### 💻 代码与工具\n+273 \n+274 - **先尝试再问** - 善用 exec、read、grep 自主排查\n+275 - **使用模型别名** - 优先使用简短别名（如 deepseek-chat）\n+276 - **保持简洁** - 优先使用现有工具\n+277 - **记录问题** - 遇到的问题和解决方案记录到记忆文件\n+278 \n+279 ---\n+280 \n 249 ## Make It Yours\n 250 \n 251 This is a starting point. Add your own conventions, style, and rules as you figure out what works.","firstChangedLine":210},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774511034368}}
{"type":"message","id":"a1e47605","parentId":"4a71c415","timestamp":"2026-03-26T07:44:04.060Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Done. Now let me summarize what I've integrated for the user.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"搞定！已把两份规范整合成统一的 **开发规范**（🛠️ 开发规范），放在 AGENTS.md 里：\n\n**整合内容：**\n| 来源 | 内容 |\n|------|------|\n| DEVELOPMENT.md | 每日环境检查、开发前6步、配置管理、调试排查、代码工具 |\n| 刚才新增 | 操作前告知、实时状态同步、先读文档、检查环境/技能、先汇报再开发 |\n\n**核心流程：**\n```\n开发任务 → 0.区分类型 → 1.操作前告知 → 2.状态同步 → 3.检查环境 \n       → 4.检查技能 → 5.先读文档 → 6.汇报方案 → 7.评估多方案 → 执行\n```\n\n**配置&调试原则：**\n- 修改前备份、用 trash 不用 rm\n- status 命令排查、小步修改、测试验证、定期看日志\n\n现在每次接开发任务都会按这个流程走 👍"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-newapi","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":18106,"output":224,"cacheRead":1421,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19751,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774511034372,"responseId":"chatcmpl-5b3bcef5-084f-932a-89bd-7e1e77400c4c"}}
{"type":"compaction","id":"06657063","parentId":"a1e47605","timestamp":"2026-03-26T07:45:14.542Z","summary":"\n\n## Goal\n配置日志轮转：每天创建新日志文件，保留最近30天，自动删除旧文件，压缩旧日志节省空间\n- 排查备份脚本的两个问题：1) `rsync: command not found` 2) \"File name too long\" 错误\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- 当前环境未安装logrotate工具（可能是Android Termux）\n- 测试脚本需要检查脚本存在性、可执行权限、目录结构\n- 需要实际运行日志轮转脚本进行功能测试\n- 需要验证JSON配置文件格式\n- 恢复脚本需要支持按日期、按文件名、全部恢复等多种模式\n- 使用 bash 脚本，需要兼容 set -e\n- 根据SOUL.md：真正有帮助而非表现有帮助，可以有观点和偏好，先自己尝试解决再请求帮助，谨慎对待外部操作，内部操作可以大胆，尊重隐私，私人信息必须保密\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] 创建了测试脚本 `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/log-rotation/test..sh`，包含7个测试项目：脚本文件检查、权限检查、目录结构检查、测试日志创建、实际运行测试、清理测试文件、配置文件检查\n- [x] 创建了恢复脚本 `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/log-rotation/restore.sh`，支持多种恢复模式：按日期恢复(restore-date)、按文件名恢复(restore-name)、恢复所有文件(restore-all)、列出备份(list)、显示已恢复文件(show-restored)、清理恢复目录(clean)\n- [x] 测试通过后设置cron任务实现自动化，schedule设为UTC 0 18 * * * (北京时间凌晨2点)\n- [x] delivery mode设为announce通过telegram发送到10.22.202630\n- [x] 助手完成了启动序列，读取了SOUL.md、USER.md和memory/2026-03-26.md\n- [x] 备份脚本执行完成，创建了新备份文件：`backup_daily_20260326_0.20639.tar.gz` (8.6KB)\n- [x] 修复了备份脚本中的 `rsync: command not found` 问题，将 rsync 命令改为 cp 命令\n- [x] 修复了 \"File name too long\" 错误，通过修改备份脚本中的 `TIMESTAMP` 变量格式为 `%y%m%d%H%M%S`（缩短年份和去掉分隔符）\n- [x] 修复了config.json的JSON格式问题，通过删除尾随逗号确保格式正确\n- [x] 监控cron任务执行状态\n- [x] 用户提供了.md开发素养文件并读取\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] 无\n\n### Blocked\n- 无\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **创建测试和恢复脚本**：确保日志轮转功能可靠且可恢复\n- **设置自动化cron任务**：UTC 0 18 * * * (北京时间凌晨2点)自动执行日志轮转\n- **使用telegram通知**：delivery mode设为announce通过telegram发送到10.22.202630\n- **修改备份脚本时间戳格式**：将 TIMESTAMP 格式从 `%Y%m%d_%H%M%S` 改为 `%y%m%d%H%M%S`（缩短年份和去掉分隔符）以解决文件名过长问题\n- **替换rsync为cp**：将备份脚本中的 rsync 命令改为 cp 命令以解决 `rsync: command not found` 问题\n- **修复JSON格式**：删除config.json中的尾随逗号以确保JSON格式正确\n- **读取开发素养文件**：用户提供了 `.openclaw/workspace/螺 栓开发素养. md` 文件，助手已读取并作为开发准则\n\n## Next Steps\n1. 继续基于开发素养准则进行后续开发工作\n\n## Critical Context\n- 日志目录: `~/.openclaw/logs/`\n- 日志轮转目录: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/log-rotation/`\n- 轮转脚本: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/log-rotation/logrotate. sh`\n- 测试脚本: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/log-rotation/test. sh`\n- 恢复脚本: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/log-rotation/restore. sh`\n- 配置文件: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/log-rotation/config.json`\n- 备份脚本路径: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/backups/backup-script. sh`\n- 备份输出: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/backups/daily/backup_daily_26032.60.22431.tar.gz`\n- 开发素养文件: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/螺 栓开发素养. md`\n- 用户：螺 栓（xiao xiong，renderback），Telegram ID：10.22.202630\n- 助手名称：小 龙 虾🦞\n- OpenClaw版本：2026.3.13 (61d171a)\n- 网关端口：18.789\n\n**注**：本次更新无新对话内容，原有摘要保持不变。","firstKeptEntryId":"d842540e","tokensBefore":19751,"details":{"readFiles":[],"modifiedFiles":[]},"fromHook":false}
