{"type":"message","id":"a5bc037f","parentId":"2a7e40f9","timestamp":"2026-03-26T10:34:23.074Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking:\n1. Can I read phone files, execute specific commands, and control certain apps?\n2. The system notes that an exec process was killed (SIGKILL) at 09:29:07 UTC\n3. User wants to switch to minimax2.5 model because it's laggy\n\nLet me address these:\n\n1. **Phone capabilities**: Currently I'm running in a PRoot Debian environment on what appears to be an Android device (Termux). I have access to:\n   - The file system within the PRoot container (which is separate from the host Android system)\n   - I cannot directly access Android-specific paths like /sdcard, /data/data, etc. unless they're mounted\n   - I can execute commands within the container environment\n   - I cannot control Android apps directly - that would require ADB or specific Android APIs\n\n2. **Model switch**: User wants to switch to minimax2.5 model. I can use session_status to set a per-session model override, or I should inform them about model aliases.\n\nLooking at my available aliases:\n- MiniMax-2.5: custom-newapi/MiniMax-2.5\n\nLet me switch the model for this session.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n1. **手机操作能力**：\n   - ✅ 执行命令：在 PRoot 容器内可以（查看文件、运行脚本等）\n   - ⚠️ 读取手机文件：只能访问容器内文件，Android 核心目录（/data/data 等）需要额外挂载\n   - ❌ 控制应用：无法直接控制 Android 应用（需要 ADB 或特殊 API）\n\n简单说：我现在在你的\"容器\"里运行，看不到手机主系统的应用和数据。\n\n2. **切换模型**：好嘞，换 MiniMax-2.5\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7218e365eb6a4f4f9cbb4141","name":"session_status","arguments":{"model":"MiniMax-2.5"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-newapi-epsq-cn","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":17427,"output":397,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17824,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774520947964,"responseId":"chatcmpl-36d1df86b962731c